The paper discusses the use of Reinforcement Learning and Evolutionary Algorithms for Neural Architecture Search, which are all subfields of Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The benchmarks used in the experiments include text classification and image classification, which are subfields of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Computer Vision (cs.CV), respectively. The paper also mentions the exploration of a vast search space, which is a common theme in Neural Evolution (cs.NE) research.
